<br>
I have cancer.  I have a form of cancer called Renal Cell Carcinoma.  In December of 2002, my left kidney was removed.  NEVER, would I want anyone to have to go through what I have gone through.  I wouldn't want to believe someone had cancer, only to find out later that it wasn't true.  <br>
<br>
Now, not many people know whether or not this is true.  PoChath knows as he is my roommate, PoSabrosia and PoTiline know because they saw my extended leave from EQ for my surgery and PoSabrosia is part of my support list (an email list) for people with RCC (and their familys/friends).<br>
<br>
So, in an online gaming type of situation it is hard to know what people tell you is true.  Alot of it comes from the fact that you either A. Meet them in real life or B.  Take their word for it.  I think though that telling people you have a disease is quite wrong when you don't really have the disease.<br>
<br>
Now for some people (lumping myself in this category) when you find out you have something like cancer or what not, we do talk about it as it helps to cope and come to an understanding about it.  (This is one of the reasons I have no fear talking about my cancer - I am trying to deal with the fact that I have it).  <br>
<br>
So, as I deviated majorly from the main point...I think it is wrong to tell people you have a disease (even when your intentions are noble) when you really do not have that disease. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://myweb.cableone.net/altfetish/kayatta2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561049">Don't peek at my underwear!!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kuladen>kuladen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Greatest,<br>
